subSubSection.paragraph:
Male genitalia (
Figs 11–17
).

Pygofer wide (in lateral view), with distinctly convex hind margins (
Fig. 11
). Anal tube wide, narrow in basal part, with convex lateral margins and hind margin deeply concave (in dorsal view). Dorsal surface of the tube with two lateral carinae (
Figs 14, 15
, 
b
). Anal column narrow, long, about 1/3 as long as anal tube. Plate of style longer than wide, with caudo-dorsal angle widely rounded (
Fig. 16
). Capitulum of style elongate, without neck, not narrowing apically (in dorsal view) (
Fig. 17
). Short hairs scattered on the surface of style. Phallobase wide, strongly curved (in lateral view). Dorso-lateral phallobase lobes wide, narrowing apically, fused dorsally (
Fig. 11
). Venral phallobase lobe long, enlarged apically, with two narrow and long latero-apical processes (
Fig. 12
). Apical aedeagal processes weakly furcated apically (
Fig. 13
). Ventral aedeagal hooks long, nearly half as long as aedeagus directed downwars and back, supported by lateral lobes of the phallobase (
Figs 11, 12
, 
a
). Connective long.
